The paper deals with the problem of computing a sparse Fourier transform, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.IT, cs.SP). The algorithm proposed in the paper is dimension-free and achieves a strong $\ell_\infty/\ell_2$ guarantee, which suggests that it may be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper introduces a new approach to the sparse Fourier transform problem, which could be of interest to researchers in data structures (cs.DS).
